column29: You probably should make HITs that don't automatically download suspicious files onto people's computers
I copied everything from the file it downloaded. Hopefully i did it right.
Make it much clearer what the code is please, I'm not sure I even pasted the right thing
Maybe make the survey code a bit shorter instead of a whole browser length worth.
The code page seemed possibly broken, I'm not sure.

It would be helpful to provide a bit more about what the rating should be about - if the heat map includes one pet, but not another, is that a good rating, or a poor rating? Also, I didn't like that it automatically downloaded something to my computer - even if the intentions were good, that feels unsafe.

Better fix the survey consent form promising $10.00 for completions in one hour! Also how was I supposed to react to multiple animals. The system seemed unable to focus on more than one animal at a time. And laslty completion code given was a json file, I just copy pasted what was on the file.
The code was a bit confusing but I think I submitted it correctly.
problem to download code, i think this is correct code
